# Project Title

Retail Demand & Inventory Analytics: Optimizing Inventory and Sales Performance.

#  Problem

A retail company operates multiple stores selling products across different categories. The company is experiencing challenges in managing inventory efficiently. 
Some products frequently run out of stock, leading to missed sales opportunities, while others remain overstocked, increasing storage costs and tying up capital.
Additionally, management lacks visibility into how promotions, pricing, seasonal trends, and store performance influence product demand. Without data-driven insights,
inventory replenishment and business decisions are often reactive rather than strategic.
The company wants to analyze historical inventory and sales data to improve inventory planning, optimize sales performance, and support better business decision-making.

# Project Objective

The primary objective of this project is to analyze historical retail sales and inventory data to identify demand patterns, evaluate inventory performance, and uncover actionable business insights.
The analysis aims to:
Improve inventory management by identifying stockout and overstock situations.
Evaluate sales performance across stores, products, and categories.
Measure the impact of promotions and seasonal factors on demand.
Support inventory replenishment decisions using historical trends.
Provide an interactive dashboard to help stakeholders monitor key business metrics.

# Business Goals
Reduce stockouts
Reduce excess inventory
Improve inventory turnover
Increase sales through better planning
Identify high-performing and low-performing products
Support data-driven decision making


